This paper focuses on investigating Android obfuscation techniques, which is related to computer security (cs.CR) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses specific obfuscation approaches such as identifier renaming and Java reflection, which are related to programming languages (cs.PL) and system and information theory (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper uses statistical analysis to draw conclusions, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG).
